  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Operating envelope explicitly bounded: axial compressive load 0–2500 N, bending moment 0–15 N·m, titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V, screw diameter 7.5 mm ± 0.05 mm, polyethylene block surrogate cortical bone. Validation experiments sample boundary points of this envelope.",
